The paper introduces an approach to detecting inconsistencies in large biological networks using Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The methodology presented involves analyzing large-scale data sets, which could fall under the subcategories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of ASP to provide explanations for inconsistencies, which could be related to the subfield of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the application of this approach to identify missing reactions suggests a connection to Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
